File: Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - Late Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu will be laid to rest on Thursday. He passed away this week after battling lung cancer since 2018. READ: Tributes pour in for Kimi Makwetu President Cyril Ramaphosa is among those who've praised Makwetu, saying he served his country with dedication, distinction, and great integrity. A memorial service will be held on Tuesday. Due to COVID-19, it'll be a private ceremony with a restriction on the number of people attending.